name: 2-(1-pyrrolidinyl)phenol
Reason: 2-(1-pyrrolidinyl)phenol has a basic unit of phenol, which has a melting point of 106°C. The pyrrolidinyl group can increase the melting point due to the presence of a nitrogen atom, which can participate in hydrogen bonding and increase the molecular weight. The estimated increase in melting point due to the pyrrolidinyl group is around +10°C.
